			<description><![CDATA[<p>
We are looking for an experienced marketing manager to manage all aspects of product marketing for our company.</p>
<p>
Join <strong>ReTargeter</strong> for the opportunity to advance your career as part of a driven and passionate team. Your skill in building long-term relationships and dedication to client success will make your contributions invaluable. Grow as a key member of our team and become an expert in the advertising and media agency landscape. We value employee development and welcome those who are lifelong learners.</p>
<p>
We are looking for intelligent and empathetic individuals who are prepared to make substantive contributions to overall marketing strategy, while also laying the foundation for building a team of their own. The responsibilities of this role are as follows:</p>
<p>
<br />
<u><strong>Content Strategy</strong></u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage the editorial calendar for our digital marketing blog</li>
<li>
Write blog posts for both our blog and for guest blogs</li>
<li>
Plan and produce evergreen content (white papers, ebooks, infographics, etc.)</li>
<li>
Track content metrics, and align content strategy with broader marketing objectives</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><u>Email Marketing</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Manage all outbound email campaigns, including nurture and drip campaigns</li>
<li>
Work closely with the Sales and Product teams to develop messaging</li>
<li>
Conduct A/B tests and track metrics for all campaigns</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><u>Sales Enablement</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work closely w/Creative Lead to plan and produce all client-facing sales collateral (decks, one sheets, case studies, etc.)</li>
<li>
Provide messaging and research support to the Sales team on an as-needed basis</li>
<li>
Serve as a liaison between the Product team and Sales team, and conduct product training seminars as necessary</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><u>Product Marketing</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Write copy for our website and Dashboard</li>
<li>
Create educational resources for the Dashboard (walkthroughs, screencasts, FAQs, etc)</li>
<li>
Work closely with Product &amp; Engineering teams on an ongoing basis</li>
<li>
Write copy for landing pages on an as-needed basis</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><u>Special Projects</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Provide social media support to Marketing and Events Manager</li>
<li>
Provide ad copywriting support to Marketing Analyst</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><u>Requirements:</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree</li>
<li>
Min 2-3 years experience in a product marketing or senior copywriting role</li>
<li>
Outstanding writing and research ability; extensive writing experience in a variety of media (short form, long form, educational, sales, etc.)</li>
<li>
Prior experience with sales copywriting, inbound marketing, and email marketing</li>
<li>
Prior experience with the following tools and concepts a major plus: SEO, HTML/web design, A/B testing, landing page optimization, WordPress, Google Analytics, HubSpot, Salesforce, Google AdWords, Adobe Illustrator)</li>
<li>
Previous experience with online advertising and advertising technology a major plus</li>
<li>
Solid understanding of marketing metrics and analytical methods</li>
<li>
Excellent initiative and interpersonal communications skills; ability to collaborate and work well with others is a must</li>
<li>
Love of reading, writing and learning</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong><u>Perks:</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Full health benefits (including dental and vision)</li>
<li>
Gym membership</li>
<li>
Daily catered lunches</li>
<li>
Beautiful office in the Financial District with gorgeous city views</li>
<li>
Fully-stocked kitchen with more snacks and goodies than you can shake a stick at</li>
<li>
Frequent team outings (including dinners, happy hours, and company retreats)</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
